results.name: Air Jordan 32 Low PF 'Win Like '96'
results.story: The special edition ‘Win Like ’96’ version of the Air Jordan 32 Low PF showed off its contemporary woven construction with this Chicago Bulls-inspired colorway. The Flyknit construction is highlighted in red, providing a snug fit and lightweight support. Underfoot, an icy translucent outsole tops off Zoom Air cushioning enhanced by FlightSpeed tech for maximum energy return.

results.name: Air Jordan 2 Retro Low Pe 'Mike Bibby'
Air Jordan 32 Low GS 'Win Like 82'
results.story: Designed by Tate Kuerbis, the Air Jordan 32 Low GS calls upon iconic elements of past models, reinventing them in a modern expression. This 'Win Like '82 kids' sneaker launched in November 2017 in homage to Michael Jordan's collegiate team. The Flyknit and leather upper is detailed with integrated laces, a diamond patterned collar and MJ's 'Ceiling is the Roof' motto under the tongue. A translucent Zoom Air sole calls out its signature Flightspeed technology.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro Low 'Mike Bibby Player Exclusive'
Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Win Like '82' Special Box
Air Jordan 20 3/4 'Mike Bibby Player Exclusive'
results.story: The Air Jordan 20 3/4 is an unreleased player exclusive shoe created for former Sacramento Kings point guard Mike Bibby in 2006. The sneaker boasts a colorway inspired by the Kings' away jerseys—black, Stealth and purple. It comes with a premium leather upper with detailed embossing and shiny patent leather on the toe and heel. Its black midsole displays 69 dimples, a nod to Michael Jordan's highest-scoring point total in a game, while a multidirectional outsole with circular patterns finishes the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 9 Retro Low 'Mike Bibby Player Exclusive'
ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg x Nice Kicks 2.0
results.story: Ronnie Fieg, designer and founder of footwear boutique Kith, joined with ASICS and Nice Kicks for this take on the Gel-Lyte 3. The lightweight running shoe sports a grey tonal colorway, a departure from Fieg’s often-colorful designs. Only the laces and midsole provide contrasting color, and the signature split tongue and Gel cushioning are included. The shoe dropped in 2010 and was exclusively sold at Nice Kicks in Austin as well as at David Z.

results.name: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg x Nice Kicks 1.0
results.story: Limited to only 250 pairs, this 2009 collaboration between online sneaker magazine Nice Kicks and ASICS was part of the Trilogy Project curated by Ronnie Fieg for New York City footwear retailer David Z. The Nice Kicks x Gel Lyte 3 'Trilogy Project’ sports a bright red upper with grey and white accents. The runner is also distinguished by its unique blend of materials, combining perforated pig skin suede on the toe box and side panels with a nubuck toe cap, ballistic mesh on the tongue and ankle and 3M reflective patent leather accents.

results.name: Jordan Lunar Grind Gatorade Like Mike
Jordan XXXII Low Like Mike Gatorade
results.story: In 1992, Michael Jordan starred in a Gatorade commercial that has since become a cult classic. As a tribute to this unforgettable commercial, Nike released a Gatorade-themed exclusive. The Air Jordan 32 Low 'Gatorade' features a white-based Flyknit upper with a toggle lacing system for an adaptive fit. The sneaker also boasts orange accents predominantly on the inner tongue and ankle, as well as Pipe Green detailing on the Jumpman and Wings branding. Keep an eye out for “Be Like Me” lettering on the inner tongue and a uniquely detailed outsole.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Gatorade Like Mike White
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Gatorade’ pays tribute to Michael Jordan’s 1991 ‘Be Like Mike’ Gatorade commercial. The shoe features the same color blocking as the OG ‘Carmine’ colorway, with a white leather upper, Gatorade-themed Team Orange accents, and a green lace lock. The spot’s slogan – “If I could be” – also hits up the inner tongue. The ‘Gatorade’ dropped with a ‘Green Suede Gatorade' colorway in December 2017.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Gatorade Like Mike White (GS)
results.story: In 1991, Michael Jordan appeared in a commercial for Gatorade that famously coined the phrase ‘Be Like Mike.’ To celebrate 50 years of the beverage, the company remastered and re-released the spot, a move that saw Nike retro the AJ6s that Jordan wore in the commercial. This grade school size features the same color blocking as the OG ‘Carmine’ colorway, while Gatorade-themed touches can be seen on the Jumpman logo and squeeze-bottle style lace toggle. The underside of the tongue is embroidered with the words ‘If I Could Be.’

results.name: Nike Court Flare AJ1 Serena Williams Bred (W)
results.story: To celebrate Serena Williams’ 23rd major title, Nike and Jordan Brand created this women’s exclusive limited-edition hybrid of Williams’ signature tennis shoe and her favorite off-court sneaker, the Air Jordan 1. The Serena Williams x Flare AJ1 ’23' is executed with the same color blocking as the iconic ‘Bred’ Air Jordan 1, with an Air Jordan ‘Wings’ logo on the collar and Williams’ logo on the tongue and heel.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red Cement (Nike Chi)
results.story: Launching as part of Nike’s NBA All-Star 2020 Collection, this Air Jordan 3 Retro SP 'Unite' colorway is a Chicago-exclusive release, marked by ‘NIKE CHI’ branding on the black heel panel. The rest of the design is unchanged from the general-release edition of the shoe, featuring a tumbled leather upper in Fire Red. The kicks are finished with signature AJ3 details, including visible Air cushioning and elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel.

results.name: Nike Court Flare AJ1 Serena Williams Hyper Pink (W)
results.story: Nike and Jordan Brand honored Serena Williams' record-breaking 23rd Grand Slam title with the release of this NikeCourt Flare AJ1 ’23,’ a hybrid of her own Nike Court Flare tennis shoe and her favorite sneaker of all time – the Air Jordan 1. This colorway references Serena’s on-court attire at the 2016 US Open. It features a black and Hyper Pink upper with an all-white sole unit. It also includes an iconic Air Jordan Wings logo on the collar.

results.name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Nike Swoosh On Tour (2020)
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘Euro Tour’ showcases a traveling theme that underscores the international reach of the Jordan franchise. Stamped in red, the classic Wings logo stands out against the sneaker’s white leather backdrop. An added mini-Swoosh is embroidered on the lateral forefoot, complementing a larger misaligned Swoosh in the same white finish. The heel overlay is embellished with a silver tour badge that lists a dozen European cities.

results.name: Jordan New Beginnings Pack Retro High 1 & Nike Air Ship
results.story: The Air Ship PE x Air Jordan 1 'New Beginnings Pack' brings together the two silhouettes that kickstarted Michael Jordan’s partnership with Nike. Released in 1984, the Air Ship is the model that MJ wore at the start of his rookie season, before switching over to the Air Jordan 1 upon the sneaker’s release the following year. Both sneakers are finished in two-tone white and red colorways, with the Air Jordan 1 featuring a recrafted build that’s true to the high-top’s original 1985 form.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Win Like 96
results.story: For Chicago Bulls Fans, the historical significance of the Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Win Like 96’ will be abundantly clear. 1996 is the year that the Bulls capped off the regular season with a record-breaking 72 wins, on their way to a fourth NBA title in six seasons. Michael wore the Jordan 11 during that magical run, and this December 2017 release, dressed in a dazzling shade of red, honors the ’96 squad that couldn’t lose.

results.name: Jordan XXXII Low Chicago Win Like 96
results.story: The Air Jordan 32 Low ‘Win Like ‘96’ borrows influence from Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls’ 1996 championship season, which included a then-record 72 wins in the regular season. The red Flyknit application on the forefoot is paired with black leather and mesh accents on the heel, with Jordan branding that’s reminiscent of the Air Jordan 2. The only deviation from Bulls colors is the icy translucent outsole underfoot.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Win Like 96 (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro TD 'Win Like '96' sneaker pays homage to Michael Jordan and the 1996 Chicago Bulls in a kids’ version of the iconic design. Led by MJ in the Air Jordan 11s, the ‘96 Bulls broke a regular season record with 72 wins, followed by a fourth championship ring. The kid-friendly ‘Win Like 96’ iteration features a Gym Red upper with Velcro straps supporting the ankle, finished with a tonal patent leather mudguard and an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Win Like 96 (PS)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro PS 'Win Like '96' sneaker pays homage to Michael Jordan and the 1996 Chicago Bulls in a Gym Red color scheme in kids' sizing. Led by MJ in the Air Jordan 11s, the ‘96 Bulls won a record-breaking 72 games in the regular season before earning their fourth championship ring. The ‘Win Like 96’ iteration of the iconic sneaker features an all-red upper, incorporating the silhouette’s statement patent leather mudguard and icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro UNC Win Like 82
results.story: Michael Jordan’s habit of lofting game-winning shots on the big stage started early, when the 19-year-old freshman nailed a jumper to put the Tar Heels up for good during the 1982 NCAA Championship game. The Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Win Like 82’ celebrates the start of MJ’s winning ways, featuring UNC team colors on a traditional AJ11 build, combining ballistic mesh, patent leather, and an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Win Like 96 (GS)
results.story: Released December 2017, Nike’s Air Jordan 11 Retro GS 'Win Like '96' sneaker pays tribute to the Chicago Bulls 1996 championship season. The kids’-sized mid top features a bright Gym Red exterior, highlighted by the iconic Jumpman logo. The breathable mesh upper is accented by a glossy patent leather mudguard. A cushioned midsole and translucent rubber outsole provide added comfort and traction.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro UNC Win Like 82 (Preschool)
results.story: Honoring Michael Jordan’s playing days at the University of North Carolina, the Air Jordan 11 Retro PS ‘Win Like ‘82’ appears with the school’s colors as a tribute to the team’s 1982 NCAA title. Featuring a white mesh upper, the shoe implements a navy patent leather along the mudguard, with Carolina Blue accents on the Jumpman branding and translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan XXXII Low UNC Win Like 82 (GS)
results.story: The Air Jordan 32 Low ‘Win Like ‘82’ features a breathable Flyknit upper in Carolina blue. The shoe’s colorway and moniker allude to the origins of Michael Jordan’s winning ways, when he hit the title-clinching shot for the University of North Carolina Tar Heels during the championship game of the 1982 NCAA Tournament. The inside of the tongue sports a reference to Michael’s famous quote, ‘The floor is the ceiling.’

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro UNC Win Like 82 (GS)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro GS 'Win Like '82' debuted in November of 2017 as an homage to Michael Jordan's first championship win. The white leather and mesh upper, bedecked with Midnight Navy patent leather, pays tribute to MJ's ritual of saluting his alma mater by wearing his collegiate practice shorts under his professional uniform. This kids' shoe has embroidered Jumpman logos at the counter and carbon fiber plate—both in University Blue—to celebrate the legacy of the champ's Tar Heels victory.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro UNC Win Like 82 (TD)
results.story: The ‘Win Like '82’ offering of the Air Jordan 11 Retro commemorates Michael Jordan’s playing days at the University of North Carolina, specifically the Tar Heels’ NCAA title in 1982. Featuring a white mesh upper with a Midnight Navy patent leather mudguard, this toddlers’ shoe also implements University Blue accents on the Jumpman branding.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Chicago Win Like 96 (I) Gift Pack
Nike x Nexus Zoom Air 'Dark Stucco'
Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit Hi 'Black'
results.story: The Chuck Taylor sneaker has revolutionized basketball footwear since 1917. Expanding the silhouette’s legacy, Converse released an update on the classic Chuck Taylor reimagined with Flyknit technology. The high top features a Flyknit upper dressed in a black color scheme, a padded collar, oversized tongue, and a Lunarlon insole for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit Low 'Black'
Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit Hi 'True Indigo'
Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit High 'Wolf Grey'
Run Star Hike High 'Tri-Panel'
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike High ‘Tri-Panel’ transforms the classic silhouette into a fashion-forward platform sneaker with a color-blocked design. The poly-canvas upper features varying tan shades on each side panel, along with pastel pink hues on the tongue and webbing pull tab. On the medial side, a circular All Star patch adorns the ankle, while a pair of chrome eyelets add to the sneaker’s breathability. A contrasting black pinstripe gives way to the stacked foam midsole, supported by high-traction rubber under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit Low 'Casino Team Red'
Nike x Chuck Taylor All Star Flyknit High 'Dark Atomic Teal Igloo'
Run Star Hike 'Tonal Marble - Rose Taupe'
Converse Run Star Hike Sunblocked Total Orange
Run Star Hike High 'Metallic Classics - Black'
Converse Run Star Hike JW Anderson White
results.story: Debuting at Jonathan Anderson’s London runway in September 2018, the J.W. Anderson x Run Star Hike ‘White’ fuses the upper of a Converse Chuck Taylor with the injection-molded tooling of the vintage Converse Run Star. Details include a stacked midsole, sawtooth tread pattern on the outsole, and ‘1917’ printed next to the All Star patch on the canvas upper – an allusion to the birth year of the Chuck Taylor.

results.name: Run Star Hike High 'Court Green Gum'
Wmns Run Star Hike High 'Light Zitron'
Converse Run Star Hike Sunblocked Moonstone Violet
Converse Run Star Hike Hi Rapid Teal
Converse Run Star Hike Hi University Red
Converse Run Star Hike Hi White Black Gum
Converse Run Star Hike Hi JW Anderson Black
results.story: UK-based label J.W. Anderson partnered with Converse to reimagine an all-star original. Revealed in June 2019 in a 'Black Gum' colorway, the J.W. Anderson x Run Star Hike aligns with the designer's penchant for pushing fashion boundaries. The traditional black canvas upper is decorated with unique accouterment including '1917' stitched to the inner right shoe to honor Converse's birthday and a red star at the back of the exaggerated heel design. Massive traction below contributes to the eye-catching look.

results.name: Converse Run Star Hike Ox Black White Gum
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike Low ‘Black Gum’ features the traditional canvas upper of the iconic Chuck Taylor All Star, complete with chrome eyelets, contrast stitching and a durable white rubber toe cap. The sneaker’s tooling is radically overhauled with a platform midsole and two-piece color-blocked outsole. Black rubber wraps up the heel, while gum rubber extends up the toe, both configured in a sawtooth pattern for optimal grip.

results.name: Run Star Hike High 'Black Ice - Black Silver'
Run Star Hike Low 'Alt Exploration - Midnight Navy'
results.story: Dropping as part of the brand’s outdoor-inspired ‘Alt Exploration’ collection, the Converse Run Star Hike Low ‘Midnight Navy’ features a coated textile upper with a thin canvas tongue, chrome eyelets, contrast stitching and a reinforced rubber toe cap — remnants of the original Chuck Taylor design on which the shoe is based. The minimalist build is mounted on an elevated platform midsole, supported by an exaggerated rubber tread under the heel and forefoot.

results.name: Converse Run Star Hike Hi JW Anderson Glitter
results.story: Designer Jonathan Anderson is no stranger to pushing the boundaries of fashion. Proving the point, the May 2019 J.W. Anderson x Run Star Hike collaboration with Converse defies convention by taking elements from the Chuck 70 and Run Star silhouettes to create a contemporary, head-turning look. The premium upper dazzles with blue, pink and green glitter and sits atop a rugged Run Star foam midsole and rubber outsole combo. Adding nostalgia, a retro All-Star logo hits the ankle to finalize the design.

results.name: Run Star Hike High 'Black Ice - Ash Stone'
Converse Run Star Hike Hi Twisted Resort (W)
Run Star Hike High 'Metallic Classics - Smoke Pink'
Run Star Hike Low 'Black Ice - Salt Pink'
Converse Run Star Hike High Concrete Heat Black
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike High ‘Concrete Heat’ updates the classic high-top with a chunky platform midsole, reinforced underfoot with a color-blocked two-piece rubber outsole that extends up the toe and heel for superior traction. Up top, the black textile build is appointed with signature details that stay true to the classic Chuck Taylor aesthetic, including a rubber toe cap, chrome eyelets and a circular All Star ankle patch.

results.name: Converse Run Star Hike Hi Black White Gum
Wmns Run Star Hike High 'Black Saffron Yellow'
Converse Run Star Hike High Concrete Heat White
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike High ‘Concrete Heat’ delivers a fashion-forward take on the iconic Chuck Taylor All Star. The lightweight upper, constructed from semi-translucent white textile with chrome eyelets and classic All Star ankle patches, sits on an exaggerated platform midsole for plush cushioning. Underfoot, a high-traction outsole in pink and gum rubber extends up the heel and toe to deliver superior grip.

results.name: Converse Run Star Hike Ox Cozy Club Black
Converse Run Star Hike Ox White Black Gum
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike Low ‘White’ delivers a fashionable twist on the classic Chuck Taylor All Star. The organic cotton canvas upper is mostly unchanged from the original, complete with chrome eyelets, a rubber toe cap and black pinstripe detailing. The sneaker’s tooling is reworked with a platform midsole and a decoupled sawtooth outsole, featuring black rubber that extends over the heel and gum rubber that wraps up the toe.

results.name: Run Star Hike High 'Alt Exploration - Light Field Surplus'
results.story: Releasing as part of the brand’s outdoor-inspired ‘Alt Exploration’ series, the Converse Run Star Hike High ‘Light Field Surplus’ showcases a pale green finish on the coated textile upper. An All Star ankle patch, chrome eyelets and a reinforced rubber toe cap give a nod to the Chuck Taylor, the classic silhouette from which the shoe takes inspiration. The high-top rides on a chunky platform midsole, reinforced by durable, high-traction rubber under the heel and forefoot.

results.name: Converse Run Star Hike Ox Dark Moss White Gum
results.story: The Converse Run Star Hike Low ‘Dark Moss’ treats the iconic Chuck Taylor All Star to a fashion-forward makeover, highlighted by a platform midsole and a two-piece color-blocked rubber outsole, rendered in a jagged sawtooth design for enhanced traction. Up top, an olive green finish is applied to the organic cotton canvas build, accented with contrast white stitching and reinforced with a signature rubber toe cap.

results.name: Chuck Taylor All Star Side Zip Hi 'Nine Iron'
Converse Run Star Hike Hi Cozy Club Light Orewood Brown
Converse Run Star Hike High Made With Love Valentines Day (2021)
New Balance 1500 Nice Kicks (2011)
results.story: The long-standing sneaker blog, Nice Kicks, teamed up with New Balance on the 1500 silhouette for a premium rendition of the heritage offering. Applying the Nice Kicks color scheme of grey-white-red throughout the design, the shoe is constructed with an assortment of perforated leather and suede panels. The shoe sports New Balance’s Encap cushioning underfoot.

results.name: "New Balance 1600 Nice Kicks ""Grand Anse"""
results.story: Texas-based sneaker blog Nice Kicks teamed up with New Balance in 2014 on this limited edition of the 1600 Grand Anse. The twist on the retro runner takes inspiration from the beach of the same name on the Caribbean island of Grenada where Nice Kicks founder Matt Halfhill once resided. Its mixed-blue mesh and nubuck is a nod to the water at Grand Anse while grey leather layers and a grey tongue symbolize the sea-washed gravel unique to the area. The layered upper is mounted on an Abzorb midsole in white with blue accents and a blue rubber outsole.

results.name: 1500.9 Made in England 'Summer Nine Pack - Purple'
Nike Air Huarache Nice Kicks Low Rider
results.story: The Nice Kicks x Huarache 'Lowrider' celebrates the opening of the first Nice Kicks retail store in downtown Los Angeles. A limited July 2016 exclusive release, te sneakers is inspired by Crenshaw's famous lowrider culture, the colorway features a white leather upper with an iridescent heel strap. A suede blue lowrider-inspired colorway dubbed the Undefeated x Air Huarache Run Premium QS 'Los Angeles' also dropped in July of 2016.

results.name: Nike Big Nike High Spike Lee
Nike Nike Rosheru Winter Dark Due (W)
Nike Air Max 1 Nike Lab Royal
results.story: The Air Max 1 Royal by NikeLab takes the first Air Max and reworks it with a deconstructed aesthetic, featuring a tonal suede upper with a premium leather sockliner. The vegetable-tanned look of the leather also appears on the midsole shank, while the midsole itself displays the shoe’s original tooling.

results.name: Nike Kyrie 2 Drew League (Nike ID)
results.story: The Nike Kyrie 2 iD ‘Drew League’ features an assortment of black and gold hues throughout the upper, with a mesh design that works in conjunction with the gold midfoot strap for a locked-in fit. The black midsole sports gold flakes and a gold Swoosh, while the translucent icy outsole implements a curved design. The shoe was given to the 2015 winners of the Drew League.

results.name: Nike Air Max 720 Saturn Nike League
Nike HyperRev 2016 Nike Fragment Wolf Grey
Nike Big Nike High Gym Red White
Nike Kybrid S2 Nike SB Sashiko Pack
Nike Killshot Beetroot
results.story: The Nike Killshot OG ‘Beetroot’ offers a simplistic two-tone colorway of the retro tennis shoe in an OG-inspired build. A rich burgundy hue floods the upper, constructed from a combination of lightweight mesh with hairy suede paneling on the heel, eyestay and toe. Contrasting white leather make its way to the Swoosh and heel tab. An exposed foam tongue and off-white rubber cupsole both contribute to the sneaker’s vintage aesthetic.

results.name: Nike Komyuter Obsidian
results.story: Released for Fall 2017, the Nike Komyuter SE 'Obsidian' sneaker matches function and durability with style in a sleek silhouette. The sock-like shoe was designed with harsh weather in mind, with a water-repellent textile upper, adjustable buckle strap across the midfoot and drawstring bungee cords at the heel counter. The shoe’s sturdy fabrication helps ensure durability and protection when it's needed most.

results.name: Nike Hyperposite Christmas
results.story: When the Boston Celtics played the Brooklyn Nets on Christmas Day 2012, Rajon Rondo stepped onto the hardwood at the Barclays Center wearing a previously unseen green and grey Air Max Hyperposite. While the design was originally a player-exclusive, a retail edition dropped the following summer. The Foamposite portion of the Air Max Hyperposite 'Rajon Rondo' extends up to the collar of the shoe, where it gives way to a Crimson lining. The midsole is fitted with a full-length Air Max cushioning unit.

results.name: Nike LunarCharge Black
results.story: Nike released a hybrid shoe that combines the cherished designs of the Air Max 90, Air Flow, Air Presto, and Air Current. The Lunarcharge Essential 'Triple Black’ features an all-black color scheme with a neoprene upper for an adaptive fit and a mesh toe box for breathability. The sneaker also sports a TPU overlay on the eyestay for structure, a sock-like collar for a snug fit, and a black Lunarlon midsole for long-lasting cushioning.

results.name: Nike KMTR Sequoia
results.story: An outdoors-inspired colorway of the classic KMTR silhouette, the KMTR Premium 'Sequoia' features a water-resistant textile upper, a midfoot strap for a locked down fit, and a heel wrap for added support. The low top also boasts sports bungee cord detailing at the heel, a tonal Swoosh on the side wall, and a thick contrasting gum rubber outsole for superior traction.

results.name: Nike Manoa Haystack
results.story: Workboot-inspired and ready for rain, the Nike Manoa boot features an all-leather, weatherproof upper in a monochrome light beige. The high shank goes up to the ankle, where you’ll find a padded collar and padded tongue—which also features a Nike All Conditions Gear brand patch. The white, foam midsole sits atop a rugged rubber outsole that's built for the outdoors, rendered in the same beige as the upper.

results.name: Nike Komyuter Birch
results.story: Nike developed the original Komyuter design almost by accident. Placing a paper bag around the foot, Nike innovators attempted to create an all-purpose, function-forward silhouette. After many iterations, the loose, 'paper bag' look took on sleek style and function with a drawcord tightening system fastened by a secondary lock-down strap across the ankle. Ready for inclement weather or temperature shifts, the Komyuter SE 'Birch' is a futuristic, versatile shoe fusing function and style.

results.name: Nike Alphadunk Hoverboard
results.story: The Nike AlphaDunk 'Hoverboard' draws inspiration from the futuristic board ridden by Michael J. Fox's character, Marty McFly, in the 1989 film Back to the Future Part II. Dressed in a vibrant color scheme similar to that of the original board—Racer Pink, Volt and black—the mid-top sneaker comes with a knit upper, pull tabs on the tongue and heel, and a translucent Swoosh. A speckled midsole, forefoot Zoom Air unit and clear outsole round out the style.

results.name: Nike Hyperposite Fireberry
results.story: Released in the spring of 2012, the Air Max Hyperposite 'Fireberry' is a shoe built for power forwards that uses design elements from the Air Foamposite and the Hyperfuse. The sneaker boasts a Hyperfuse-based black upper with Foamposite overlays in Dynamic Blue. The mid top also sports mesh window panels on the side for breathability and Fireberry accents throughout.

results.name: Nike KD13 Black
results.story: The Nike KD 13 ‘Black’ feature a minimalist color scheme on a mid-top silhouette reminiscent of its predecessor’s. The seamless black textile upper is equipped with a padded collar and heel overlay integrated into the lacing system. On the lateral side, a contrasting white Swoosh extends to the lightly speckled midsole, which houses a full-length Zoom Air unit. Underfoot, the durable rubber outsole is treated to a marbleized effect in white and grey.

results.name: Nike Cortez Floral
results.story: This vibrant Cortez Basic colorway released alongside a matching Air Force 1 to complete Nike’s two-piece Floral Pack. The retro runner features a black nylon upper printed with an all-over multicolor floral print, complemented by solid black leather overlays at the toe, heel, eyestay and Swoosh. It all rests on a crisp white midsole with a contrasting streak of black.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Iridescent (Nike ID)
Nike Air Max 97 Have a Nike Day
results.story: Nike’s release lineup for Air Max Day 2019 includes the Air Max 97 ‘Have a Nike Day.’ The tagline wraps around the upper in white-on-black print, contrasted by a lavender suede mudguard and bright teal leather overlays atop a tan mesh base. The feel-good design is finished with a circular lace jewel that offers a Swoosh-infused spin on the classic smiley-face icon.

results.name: Nike Big Nike High Kobe Bryant Lil Dez
Nike Air Force 1 Crater Nike Grind (GS)
Nike Air Max 90 Nike Grind Black (GS)
Nike NIke Free Transform Flyknit Tisci Multi-Color
results.story: NikeLab teamed up with designer Riccardo Tisci once again for a contemporary spin on the Free Transform Flyknit Sun. The shoe integrates a multicolor Flyknit construction into the upper, which forms a breathable, sock-like fit, while the Flywire cables work with the asymmetrical lacing system to provide support.

results.name: Nike Air Max 95 Have a Nike Day
results.story: Releasing as part of a larger collection celebrating Air Max Day 2019, the Air Max 95 ‘Have a Nike Day’ highlights a basic black palette with wavy pastel overlays in textile and suede. ‘Have a Nike Day’ is printed on each of the lace loops, while a stylized smiley-face icon is embroidered on the tongue. A translucent rubber outsole in lavender delivers a final pop of color.

results.name: Nike Air Max 1 Nike Lab Royal Black
results.story: The NikeLab Air Max 1 Royal offers a premium update to the classic retro runner, highlighted by a deconstructed suede upper in black. Vachetta tan leather on the midsole welt and interior heel padding, along with tonal waxed laces, add to the luxury aesthetic. The stacked midsole is finished in contrasting white and fitted with a standard encapsulated Max Air unit.

results.name: Nike Air More Money Have a Nike Day
results.story: To prepare for Air Max day in 2019, Nike released some of its most popular silhouettes with a pastel colorway and trendsetting Swoosh smiley face. The Air More Money 'Have a Nike Day' shoe showcases 'Air Money' across the lace guards and 'Have a Nike Day' embroidered on the heel. The silhouette builds on history by combining original performance Air technology with contemporary color and a positive Swoosh vibe.

results.name: Nike Air Max 270 Have a Nike Day
results.story: Smiley faces smile back while wearing Nike's Air Max 270 'Have a Nike Day.' A combination of Black, Hyper Jade and Bleached Coral come together with medal smiley face details to capitalize on the shoe's positive vibe. Just in time for Air Max Day, the Air Max 270 'Have a Nike Day' dropped in March 2019 inspired from an old Nike advertisement.

results.name: Nike Air Max Plus Sky Nike Pack (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Air Max Plus GS ‘Sky Nike’ features a shiny metallic silver finish on a breathable mesh upper, accented with reflective detailing and tonal TPU overlays that recall windswept palm trees. The retro runner sits atop a white foam midsole fitted with visible Max Air units in a contrasting Hyper Crimson hue. The midfoot is reinforced with a prominent shank plate inspired by a whale’s tail surging out of the water.

results.name: Nike Air Max 97 Sky Nike Pack (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Air Max 97 GS ‘Sky Nike’ adds reflective detailing to extra-long black laces secured with blue lace locks. Additional reflective elements are showcased on the Hyper Crimson overlays that wrap around the top portion of the upper. Distressed detailing adds a vintage aesthetic to the metallic silver mudguard, which gives way to a foam midsole fitted with a full-length Max Air unit for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Trainfusion Nine 3.0 'Cool Shadow'
results.story: Reebok’s Trainfusion Nine 3.0 gets transformed in this ‘Cool Shadow’ women’s sneaker. Built with a breathable mesh upper and detailed with synthetic overlays, this edition is dressed in a colorway of mostly gray hues but displays pops of vibrant teal in the sockliner. The brand’s logo appears on both the tongue and heel panel, with an EVA midsole included for cushioning. A rubber outsole designed with flex grooves helps provide a smooth stride.

results.name: Wmns One Cushion 3.0 Nite 'Asteroid Dust'
results.story: The Reebok Wmns One Cushion 3.0 Nite is a lightweight running sneaker with adaptive framework. This 'Asteroid Dust' women's iteration utilizes a breathable SmoothFuse mesh upper with reflective NanoWeave Support overlays and a stabilizing external TPU heel counter. Logo call-outs issue a technical note. Triple-density midsole cushioning and isolated rubber outsole pods are precisely engineered to enhance performance.

results.name: Reebok Question Mid Nice Kicks Bubba Chuck
results.story: Made in collaboration with the Austin-based sneaker boutique, the Nice Kicks x Reebok Question ‘Bubba Chuck’s Fishing’ draws inspiration from Allen Iverson’s passion for recreational fishing. The retro silhouette replaces traditional leather construction with an outdoor-themed build, highlighted by a black textile base with tan hairy-suede overlays. Glow-in-the-dark detailing distinguishes the speckled midsole and Reebok Vector logo atop the tongue.

results.name: Wmns Nite Jogger 'Reflective'
results.story: The women’s Nite Jogger ‘Reflective’ is designed to come to life when hit with headlights or flash photography. Otherwise, the design features a simple black textile upper with a mild iridescent sheen on the sneaker’s reflective accents. Textured surfaces on the tongue and forefoot overlay are meant to evoke deep space, while the full-length Boost midsole maintains the stealthy color scheme. Underfoot, subtle pops of violet emerge on the black rubber outsole.

results.name: Wmns Nite Jogger 'Reflective'
results.story: The women’s Nite Jogger ‘Reflective’ combines a stealthy color scheme with various light-grabbing accents. Standing out against the black textile upper are iridescent overlays treated to a high-vis reflective coating, including the signature three-stripes at the quarter panel. The retro-inspired runner rides on a full-length Boost midsole in matching black, reinforced underfoot by a two-tone black and purple rubber outsole.

results.name: The Hike 'Earth Green'
results.story: With a stylish visage and classic shape, the adidas The Hike boot is a modern take on outdoor utility. This iteration balances full-foot support and durability in a combination of 'Earth Green' textile and suede with ventilated panels and a textured midfoot overlay. Metal eyelets and cord lacing reinforce the closure system while graphic counter trim issue a fashion-forward note. Its Light Bone rubber sole has a traditional lug pattern.

results.name: Nite Jogger 'Solar Red'
results.story: As the 2019 version of adidas’ 1980s classic, the Nite Jogger 'Solar Red’ sneaker refreshes the nocturnal runner with streamlined style and technology. The durable mesh and nylon ripstop upper is paneled with suede trimmings. adidas’ Three-Stripes branding and heel tab are visible through the night with reflective detailing. Nite Jogger is completed with two layers of cushioning: a supportive OrthoLite sockliner and responsive Boost midsole.

results.name: Nite Jogger 'Signal Green'
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger ‘Signal Green’ applies a vibrant finish to the lifestyle silhouette modeled after the brand’s original reflective running shoe from the 1980s. The sneaker’s breathable mesh upper is accented with tonal reflective detailing and contrasting black hits on the heel. Similarly, the full-length Boost midsole features a gradient finish that transitions from a black heel to neon green along the forefoot.

results.name: Nite Jogger J 'Carbon'
results.story: An all-black Nite Jogger was released in April 2017. The Nite Jogger J 'Carbon' takes elements from the adult-released sneaker and inserts them into a kids’-sized version. Mesh and nylon ripstop cover the upper, trimmed with suede overlays. A heel tab and Three-Stripes branding are coated with a reflective finish. Layered with an OrthoLite sockliner and Boost midsole, the shoe helps keep small feet comfortable and protected.

results.name: Nite Jogger 'Solar Orange'
results.story: Introducing the adidas 80s runner, known for its flashy, reflective design, to a modern generation, April 2019 debuted the Nite Jogger sneaker in a 'Solar Orange' colorway. Lightweight mesh and nylon ripstop construct the upper, trimmed with soft suede overlays. The brand’s signature Three-Stripes and heel tab are outfitted with a shiny reflective finish. Underfoot, an OrthoLite sockliner and Boost midsole help provide lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Nite Jogger 'Blue Bird'
results.story: Equipped to be worn day to night, the 1980 Nite Jogger is revamped for the modern era. The adidas Nite Jogger 'Blue Bird' sneaker is constructed of a mesh and nylon ripstop upper, trimmed with suede overlays. The runner shines through the night, fitted with reflective accents on heel tab and Three-Stripes. Underfoot, an OrthoLite sockliner and Boost midsole help deliver supportive cushioning with each stride.

results.name: Nite Jogger 'Chalk White'
results.story: adidas' high-visibility runner from the 80s was re-issued in 2019 with contemporary design and technology upgrades. Arrived in June 2019, the adidas Nite Jogger 'Chalk White' combines mesh, nylon ripstop and suede in light neutrals across its upper. Reflective details hit the toe, heel and laces. A full-length Boost midsole below offers revolutionary energy-return, finished with rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Gradient
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger ‘Sunset’ rides on a full-length Boost midsole finished in a gradient blend of colors that transition from orange to blue — a polychrome shift that recalls glowing skies at dusk. Up top, the breathable black mesh upper is reinforced with tonal suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. Iridescent reflective detailing is applied to no-sew skins and signature three-stripes alike, good for added visibility as dusk turns to night.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Grey One
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger 'Signal Green' features a durable build that swaps out traditional mesh for Cordura nylon in a neutral grey hue. Leather and suede overlays continue the all-grey theme, while reflective detailing at the heel offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker’s matching grey Boost midsole is accented by a pop of Signal Green on the lateral sidewall, highlighting a barcode and factory-tag branding.

results.name: Wmns Nite Jogger 'Aero Blue'
results.story: Initially released in the leisure-running boom of the 80s, the adidas Wmns Nite Jogger is a blend of hi-vis functionality and modern street influence. This women's version—emerged in September 2019—carries a nylon ripstop and mesh upper with Aero Blue suede eyestays, reflective inserts and contrast Three-Stripes. A Morse code label adorns the tongue. The sneaker has a Boost midsole and split-colored rubber outsole for energized stability.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger SNS Exclusive
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger was the first road runner developed for after-dark activity in the late ‘70s. Modernized for a March 2018 release, this 'Sneakersnstuff Exclusive' edition brings the retro style up to speed in a ripstop and mesh upper with nubuck overlays. Reflective elements throughout illuminate at dawn or dusk as the foot is propelled forward by a Boost midsole atop multicolored rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Morse Code
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger fuses progressive design with authentic elements to continue the legacy of the German brand's first reflective runner. Emerged in September 2019, this edition in white mesh wears hairy suede panels, a 'Solar Red' heel clip and flecked laces. Wavy details add a light-catching flash under low light. Accented by a color-pop Morse code graphic, the sneaker's Boost midsole is posed above a rubber outsole for controlled energy return.

results.name: Wmns Nite Jogger 'Grey Three'
results.story: The women’s adidas Nite Jogger ‘Grey Three’ showcases a neutral color scheme on the retro-inspired lifestyle runner. Like the original Nite Jogger from 1980, the design makes use of 3M reflective accents throughout the upper, constructed from grey mesh with tonal leather overlays. Pale mint green accents appear on the laces, heel counter and rubber outsole. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Cloud White
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger was re-vamped and re-issued in 2019, providing the original high-visibility runner from the 1980s with superior tech. This 'Easy Mint' edition arrived in June of the same year, featuring lightweight mesh on the forefoot, Easy Mint and grey suede panels, and a nylon sidewall with Three-Stripes branding. Below, adidas Boost cushioning is presented in a full-length format for maximum response.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger White Grey
results.story: Inspired by adidas’ namesake runner from 1976, the Nite Jogger ‘Neutral White’ features white nylon ripstop on the quarter panel, breathable grey mesh at the toe box, and grey suede overlays throughout. Reflective accents deliver visibility during low-light conditions, while a full-length Boost midsole provides lightweight and responsive cushioning for all-day comfort.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger 3M Grey
results.story: The 3M x adidas Nite Jogger ‘3M Logo Print’ delivers a modern interpretation of the footwear industry’s first reflective running shoe, originally released in 1980 to provide added visibility during nighttime runs. In addition to reflective thread woven into the laces, the sneaker’s Metal Grey leather upper is covered in a reflective silver print made up of the 3M Scotchlite logo. A full-length Boost midsole maintains the monochromatic design.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Core Black
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger ‘Black Carbon’ combines clean lines, archival design cues and reflective properties for visibility in low-light conditions. An understated black color scheme with orange accents come to life through the reflective hits used on the shoe’s laces, Three-Stripes, heel patch and forefoot overlays. It all rests on a black Boost midsole for responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Triple Grey
results.story: Reviving the 80s after-dark runner, the adidas Nite Jogger calls upon contemporary streetwear aesthetics and modernized tech to update the classic. This 'Triple Grey' variant—released in April 2019—is shaped by a nylon ripstop and mesh upper that shines in low-light conditions via reflective Three-Stripes and overlays. Suede detailing and a TPU plug enhance durability. Responsive Boost midsole cushioning layers a durable rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger Orbit Grey
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger ‘Orbit Grey’ contrasts its understated color scheme with a pop of metallic silver on the forefoot overlay. The rest of the upper is constructed from white textile with grey suede overlays and reflective detailing throughout. Semi-translucent three-stripes adorn the sneaker’s lateral side, while the opposite side features an adidas wordmark outlined in red. The retro-inspired runner rides on a full-length Boost midsole for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Wmns Nite Jogger 'Purple Tint'
results.story: The women’s Nite Jogger 'Purple Tint' rides on a responsive Boost midsole, finished in a subtle gradient effect that transitions from pale lavender to white. Up top, the monochromatic black mesh upper is reinforced with no-sew forefoot overlays and an external heel counter in matching black. Iridescent reflective detailing on the eyelets, tongue and heel tab provide added visibility in low-light conditions.

results.name: adidas Nite Jogger 3M Barcode
results.story: The adidas Nite Jogger ‘Signal Green’ updates the retro-inspired runner with oversized 3M branding on the medial side panel. The rest of the upper is constructed from neon green textile covered in an open mesh made with 3M Carbon Black, a material that offers the brand’s brightest reflectivity. The layered build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, embellished with a unique bar code graphic on the lateral sidewall.
